      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DECALOGUE (3) led and just missed over 1625m in a Wyong Maiden, before spiking his figures running fourth in the G2 Tulloch Stakes at Rosehill over 2000m. Zac Lloyd is reunited and can use the inside barrier. Switches back to Maiden grade and sets a decent standard. CRUSADER VOYAGE (2) was tried over this trip at Group 1 level at the back of his previous preparation and presents third-up off a narrow defeat in a Super Maiden over 1600m at Hawkesbury, where he led them up. Berry sticks aboard, and the gelding has been kept up to the mark with a Rosehill trial. The blinkers come off, and he's ready for the step up in trip. SCOOP THE POOL (6) peaks off a solid effort over 1850m at Newcastle. Needs to be at his best, but JMac is a key jockey engagement, and he can fight out the finish. SARAPO (5) is fit and has been knocking on the door. He will run it out and is in the mix.",
